div1.p:






LOADER, Edwin (38, traveller), 

pleaded guilty 


of stealing a sovereign purse, the goods of 



   William Allen Simpson;


stealing five forks and two spoons, the goods of 



   William Allen Simpson;


 stealing one tea and coffee set, the goods of 



   William Allen Simpson; 


forging a receipt to a certain order for the payment of £2 6s. Id., with intent to defraud; 


forging and uttering, knowing the same to be forged, an endorsement to a certain order for the payment of £1 13s. with intent to defraud.

Sentences: Simpson and Marchant, 



                     Twelve months' hard labour; 


                     sentence upon Allen was postponed till next Session.
